articles.title: Experimental Design
articles.description:
As part of experimental design course in academics, i looked up for the parameters influancing housing prices. i used block model for this.
Score: 100
articles.contents:
2. Model and Variables Definision:
Definisions:
\(y_{ij} = \mu + \alpha_{j}+\beta_{i} + \varepsilon_{ij}\)
\(j\) = District
\(i\) = Municipal status
\(y_{ij}\) - Average salary for employees by municipal status and district
\(\mu\) - Expectation
\(\alpha_{j}\) - Impact of treatment j
\(\beta_{i}\) - Effect of block i
\(\varepsilon_{ij}\) - Random error
Model Assumptions:
\(\varepsilon_{ijk}\) ~ \(Norm(0, Var^{2})\)
Independence of observations
Assumption of Equal Variance
Model Assumptions:
\(H_{0}\): \(\alpha_{1}\)=\(\alpha_{2}\)=\(\alpha_{3}\)=\(\alpha_{4}\)
\(H_{1}\): Else
\(H_{1}\): \(\beta_{1}\)=\(\beta_{2}\)=\(\beta_{3}\)=\(\beta_{4}\)
\(H_{1}\): Else

            Bio
            Over the past decade, I have amassed valuable experience
            and expertise by working in four different organizations
            within the data center industry. Simultaneously, I pursued
            my Bachelor’s degree in industrial engineering and
            management, with a specialization in information
            systems.
            Equipped with this diverse background, I am now fully
            prepared to embark on my next challenge and seize new
            opportunities. My passion lies in the field of data, and my
            ultimate goal is to establish myself as a data analyst.
            To showcase my projects and demonstrate my capabilities,
            I have created a web page that complements my GitHub
            portfolio. This combined platform will provide you with
            comprehensive insights into my skills and
            accomplishments.
